rComments: She's a good prof. Lots of readings and assignments so it's hard to keep up but her expectations are clear and is willing to hear the students out!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Participation matters', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Not organized in presenting the material, very distracting.
Definitely one of the best PAP professors at UOttawa. Great lectures and really clear criteria.
Wallner is hands down my favourite prof at uOttawa thus far. I really enjoyed showing up to lectures for this course.

This seminar class is engaging, fun, and really interesting. Get ready to participate. Wallner starts the class with a round table and selects students throughout class to speak. There is also a challenging (but super fun) competition in this course. Warning: don't "over" participate or frequently go on long tangents... Wallner will get annoyed.

Wallner is an outstanding professor - one of the best I've had. Her lectures are really clear, and very well structured. She makes her expectations really clear at the beginning, so you know what you are in for. The exams are HARD - you must study and memorize author names. She tries hard to learn names and engages with students in a fun way.

Hands down the best professor I have ever had! She is an incredibly knowledgable prof who is concise, articulate and engaging when she lectures, making what could be a convoluted topic highly organized. She is a tough but fair marker considering you're given exam topics ahead of time. She cares about your learning and is not going to trick you.
Awesome professor. Really smart and well spoken. Too bad she only teaches one MA Public Admin course.
Hard to understand. Needs to allow students to participate more. Always seems busy and unwilling to offer help outside of class.
Found her to be a tough maker. even though her classes are clear and informative. wont bother taking another class with her.

Amazing, funny, knowledgeable and concise.  I'll be making every effort to be in her class again. She definitely renewed my interest in the program, if only she could be teaching all more courses. Readings and textbooks are insightful and clearly chosen with intent and linked to class material.
Excellent Course. Excellent Prof. Kudos to you, Prof Wallner.

Dr. Wallner is easily the most influential prof I had the pleasure of studying under at uOttawa. Having had her for 2 courses, her teaching style really allows for her to connect with students in a meaningful way, and convey subject matter in a fashion that makes it easy to retain, and exciting to attend class. Highly recommend with no hesitation!

In class , she's very interesting. Relates class material with current real world issues. Her workload, though, is heavier than average and I find her to be a pretty tough marker. Was never specific in her expectations, whether they be in the syllabus or in class, so you always had to ask. Had her in two  public policy classes, 3rd and 4th year.

Horrible professor. She's fun in class, but her repeated pauses 'to think' makes her seem very green. Worse, she talks way too much without allowing us students any input. Very little exchange leading to a very unfriendly experience. Avoid her!
Good lecturer and fun discussion groups. She also gives you exam questions ahead of time.
AMAZING WOMAN....she is extremely helpful and makes policy development interesting and interactive! One of the best prof in Public Admin, and possibly all of UOttawa

Good prof. Didn't think I'd like her at the beginning. But she's a new prof and turned out to be awesome. Really knows her stuff and is super helpful outside of class. Course workload is slightly lighter than average.
She's awesome! She makes dull material more interesting & fun. Her expectations are clear and she's really interactive with the class. I learned a lot :)
